y/Polygons/Plabel.jpg" width=3D"253" height=3D"212" alt=3D"polyparts"></div=
></td>
          <td width=3D"62%" valign=3D"top" class=3D"TimesBlack16"><p>The <s=
pan class=3D"TimesBlue16">apothem of a regular polygon</span> is a line seg=
ment from the center of the polygon perpendicular to any side of the polygo=
n.  <br>
            <br>
            <span class=3D"TimesBlue16">=CE=94 <em>DOC</em> is  an isoscele=
s triangle,</span> making the apothem the altitude of this triangle and the=
 median of this triangle (going to the midpoint <em>P</em>.)=20
